        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 25 at 4:24PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 424 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm over
Damon, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts 40 to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Talimena State Park...            Red Oak...
Gowen...                          Sardis...
Damon...                          Higgins...
Bengal...                         Panola...
Yanush...                         Robbers Cave State Park...
Wilburton...                      Albion...
Talihina...                       Hartshorne...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM CDT for
southeastern Oklahoma.</instruction>
